TITLE: From legroom to airfare: How JetBlue's takeover of Spirit could change air travel
SUMMARY: JetBlue is setting its sights on getting rid of Spirit's tight seating and basic cabins.

TITLE: Biden tests positive for Covid again, will restart isolation despite no new symptoms
SUMMARY: Biden is experiencing no new symptoms and "continues to feel quite well," Dr. Kevin O'Connor said in a memo shared by the White House.

TITLE: McDonald's and Chipotle say customers are trading down, visiting less often as inflation hits budgets
SUMMARY: McDonald's and Chipotle Mexican Grill are seeing customers trade down and visit less often as inflation pressures their budgets.

TITLE: 'Jeopardy!' locks in hosting deals for Mayim Bialik and Ken Jennings
SUMMARY: "Jeopardy!" has signed on Mayim Bialik and Ken Jennings to be hosts of the show moving forward.

TITLE: Gun CEOs call shootings 'local problems' and defend 'inanimate' weapons
SUMMARY: Major gun manufacturers have made over $1 billion in the the last decade selling assault-style weapons, according to the House Oversight panel.

TITLE: The space economy grew at fastest rate in years to $469 billion in 2021, report says
SUMMARY: The global space economy grew last year at the fastest annual rate since 2014, according to a report by the Space Foundation.

SUMMARY: Masten had won a $75 million NASA contract to deliver payloads to the moon's south pole, but the project ran far over budget.

SUMMARY: The average rate on the popular 30-year fixed mortgage fell to 5.22% on Thursday from 5.54% on Wednesday, according to Mortgage News Daily.

SUMMARY: Procter & Gamble reported mixed quarterly results and warned it expects challenges such as rising commodity costs to persist in its fiscal 2023.

TITLE: Trucking CEOs expect higher prices, potential disruptions in second half of the year
SUMMARY: U.S. trucking CEOs expect to maintain pricing power even with volumes softening as retailers, manufacturers and consumers adjust to disruptions.

SUMMARY: JetBlue's takeover of Spirit Airlines requires the blessing of the Justice Department.

SUMMARY: LIV Golf, the Saudi-backed league that has the blessing of former President Trump and Phil Mickelson, aims to build franchises.

TITLE: Here are 4 key things to consider if you actually hit the $1.28 billion Mega Millions jackpot
SUMMARY: While the odds are stacked against you snaring the top prize, it's worth giving thought to what you actually would do if you were to win.

SUMMARY: Donald Trump is considering announcing a campaign for the White House, as he faces criticism from 9/11 families for hosting a Saudi-backed golf event.

TITLE: UPS workers rally in New York to protest hot working conditions
SUMMARY: Union leaders at the rally described UPS distribution centers "infernos" with limited air conditioning.

SUMMARY: Analyst research reported lackluster demand in the U.S. for McDonald's McPlant burger, which is made using Beyond Meat patties.

SUMMARY: Best Buy said sales have slowed amid a tougher economic backdrop, as customers contend with inflation.

SUMMARY: Pilots for major airlines described opportunism and a desire to cut costs throughout the industry as worsening the situation travelers are facing today.

SUMMARY: After more than two years, New Zealand is lifting its strict border controls and is set to welcome back all international travelers on Sunday.

SUMMARY: "Mad Money" host Jim Cramer rings the lightning round bell, which means he's giving his answers to callers' stock questions at rapid speed.

SUMMARY: "The lesson, of course, is that as compelling as it is to believe in someone ... it almost never works over the long haul," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: Jim Cramer warns investors not to miss their window to buy stocks
SUMMARY: "When the Fed gets out of the way, you have a real window and you've got to jump through it," the "Mad Money" host said.

TITLE: Climate groups react to Manchin’s surprise turnaround on reconciliation bill
SUMMARY: If passed and signed into law, the reconciliation bill would be the largest climate investment ever taken by Congress.

TITLE: Bausch Health shares tank in what could be a worst-case scenario after a judge order
SUMMARY: Bausch Health said Thursday afternoon it will "consider all available options to vigorously defend" its IP and appeal.

TITLE: Ford beats expectations and raises dividend as company sells more of its top models
